<subSubSection pageId="40" pageNumber="40" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="40.[667,1194,678,1353]" pageId="40" pageNumber="40">
AMNH 6762 bears a 
<typeStatus box="[966,1016,678,699]" pageId="40" pageNumber="40">type</typeStatus>
label with the Wied name 
<taxonomicName box="[811,993,707,730]" class="Aves" family="Sylviidae" genus="Sylvia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Passeriformes" pageId="40" pageNumber="40" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="poicilotis">
<emphasis box="[811,993,707,730]" italics="true" pageId="40" pageNumber="40">Sylvia poicilotis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in what appears to be Allen’s hand, but he did not list this name in his (
<bibRefCitation author="Allen, J. A." box="[845,1001,767,789]" pageId="40" pageNumber="40" pagination="209 - 276" refId="ref112107" refString="Allen, J. A. 1889 c. On the Maximilian types of South American birds in the American Museum of Natural History. Bulletin of the American Museum of Natural History 2 (19): 209 - 276." type="journal article" year="1889">Allen, 1889c</bibRefCitation>
) paper on the Maximilian 
<typeStatus box="[816,876,797,818]" pageId="40" pageNumber="40">types</typeStatus>
in AMNH. It is labeled ‘‘not a 
<typeStatus box="[761,814,827,848]" pageId="40" pageNumber="40">type</typeStatus>
, J.T.Z[immer].’’ It is apparent, both from the original Wied label pasted on the reverse of the AMNH label and from 
<bibRefCitation author="Wied &amp; Maximilian, Prinz von" box="[667,887,915,937]" pageId="40" pageNumber="40" pagination="637 - 1277" refId="ref131007" refString="Wied, Maximilian, Prinz von. 1831. Beitrage zur Naturgeschichte von Brasilien, 3 (2): 637 - 1277. Weimar: Gr. H. S. priv. Landes-Industrie-Comptoirs." type="journal article" year="1831">Wied (1831: 715)</bibRefCitation>
that his use of 
<taxonomicName class="Aves" family="Sylviidae" genus="Sylvia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Passeriformes" pageId="40" pageNumber="40" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="poicilotis">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="40" pageNumber="40">Sylvia poicilotis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is intended as a new combination of 
<taxonomicName authority="Temminck. When" authorityName="Temminck. When" box="[703,1164,974,997]" class="Aves" family="Vireonidae" genus="Hylophilus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Passeriformes" pageId="40" pageNumber="40" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="poicilotis">
<emphasis box="[703,940,974,997]" italics="true" pageId="40" pageNumber="40">Hylophilus poicilotis</emphasis>
Temminck. When
</taxonomicName>
it was shown not to be that species, 
<bibRefCitation author="Nordmann, A." pageId="40" pageNumber="40" pagination="1 - 18" refId="ref124108" refString="Nordmann, A. 1835. I. Vogel. In A. Erman, Reise um die Erde durch Nord-Asien und die beiden Oceane in des Jahren 1828, 1829 und 1830: 1 - 18. Berlin: G. Reimer." type="journal article" year="1835">Nordmann (1835: 14)</bibRefCitation>
introduced the name 
<taxonomicName class="Aves" family="Sylviidae" genus="Sylvia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Passeriformes" pageId="40" pageNumber="40" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="amaurocephalus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="40" pageNumber="40">Sylvia amaurocephalus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, based on a Wied specimen in ZMB (
<bibRefCitation author="Hellmayr, C. E." box="[675,923,1093,1115]" pageId="40" pageNumber="40" refId="ref119559" refString="Hellmayr, C. E. 1935. Catalogue of birds of the Americas and the adjacent islands. Alaudidae - Hirundinidae - Motacillidae - Bombycillidae - Ptilogonatidae - Dulidae - Vireonidae - Vireolaniidae - Cyclarhidae - Laniidae - Sturnidae - Coerebidae - Compsothlypidae. Chicago: Field Museum of Natural History, Publication 347, Zoological Series, volume 13, Part 8, vi + 541 pp." type="book" year="1935">Hellmayr, 1935: 159</bibRefCitation>
). It is now considered a full species, 
<taxonomicName authority="(Nordmann, 1835)" baseAuthorityName="Nordmann" baseAuthorityYear="1835" class="Aves" family="Vireonidae" genus="Hylophilus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Passeriformes" pageId="40" pageNumber="40" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="amaurocephalus">
<emphasis box="[867,1193,1122,1145]" italics="true" pageId="40" pageNumber="40">Hylophilus amaurocephalus</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Nordmann, A." box="[675,878,1152,1175]" pageId="40" pageNumber="40" pagination="1 - 18" refId="ref124108" refString="Nordmann, A. 1835. I. Vogel. In A. Erman, Reise um die Erde durch Nord-Asien und die beiden Oceane in des Jahren 1828, 1829 und 1830: 1 - 18. Berlin: G. Reimer." type="journal article" year="1835">Nordmann, 1835</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
(see 
<bibRefCitation author="Willis, E. O." box="[948,1088,1153,1175]" pageId="40" pageNumber="40" pagination="559 - 567" refId="ref131107" refString="Willis, E. O. 1991. Sibling species of greenlets (Vireonidae) in southern Brazil. Wilson Bulletin 103: 559 - 567." type="journal article" year="1991">Willis, 1991</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Raposo, M. A. &amp; R. Parrini &amp; M. Napoli" pageId="40" pageNumber="40" pagination="87 - 109" refId="ref126171" refString="Raposo, M. A., R. Parrini, and M. Napoli. 1998. Taxonomia, morfometria e bioacustica do grupo expecifico Hylophilus poicilotis / H. amaurocephalus (Aves, Vireonidae). Ararajuba 6 (2): 87 - 109." type="journal article" year="1998">Raposo et al., 1998</bibRefCitation>
, and 
<bibRefCitation author="Dickinson, E. C." box="[908,1182,1182,1204]" pageId="40" pageNumber="40" refId="ref116121" refString="Dickinson, E. C. (editor). 2003. The Howard and Moore complete checklist of the birds of the world, 3 rd ed. London: Christopher Helm, 1039 pp." type="book" year="2003">Dickinson, 2003: 485</bibRefCitation>
). AMNH 6762 had been placed in the general collection, but because it bears an AMNH 
<typeStatus box="[667,717,1272,1293]" pageId="40" pageNumber="40">type</typeStatus>
label, it has been returned to the 
<typeStatus box="[1143,1193,1272,1293]" pageId="40" pageNumber="40">type</typeStatus>
collection with a separate label noting that it is not a 
<typeStatus box="[765,818,1331,1352]" pageId="40" pageNumber="40">type</typeStatus>
.
</paragraph>
